Author: ss1969 <kiilii@hotmail.com>
Date:   Tue Oct 28 09:22:56 2025 +0800

    shutdown sockets in finish routine (#504)
    
    * shutdown sockets in finish
    
    Background:
      Sockets created by accept() in schedule_request_job() will not be
    shutdown in original RunMiniServer() , it only shutdown listening
    sockets. I tried to use a LinkedList to store sockets created in
    schedule_request_job(), and shutdown() them all in RunMiniServer()
    when stopSock is set. This will help UpnpFinish() to quit quickly.
    
    Changlog:
    1, add functions help shutdown sockets created.
    2, use list feature to search/free, more reliable
    3, Free resources when finish

